tcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2560x1440+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F55%2Fef6efd044e5085e7f311ead656e6%2Fsorry-baby-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2560x1440+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F55%2Fef6efd044e5085e7f311ead656e6%2Fsorry-baby-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2560x1440+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F55%2Fef6efd044e5085e7f311ead656e6%2Fsorry-baby-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2560x1440+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F55%2Fef6efd044e5085e7f311ead656e6%2Fsorry-baby-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2560x1440+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F55%2Fef6efd044e5085e7f311ead656e6%2Fsorry-baby-1.jpg" class="img" alt="Eva Victor plays an English lit professor in Sorry, Baby." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Eva Victor plays an English lit professor in &lt;em&gt;Sorry, Baby.&lt;/em&gt;                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Mia Cioffy Henry/Courtesy of Sundance Institute/A24                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/16/nx-s1-5451376/sorry-baby-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sorry, Baby&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is about a woman trying to make sense of life after sexual assault. Though it is very much a drama, offbeat comedic smarts are throughout it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; The first half of HBO's two-part documentary &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/14/nx-s1-5467147/billy-joel-documentary-hbo-and-so-it-goes-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Billy Joel: And So It Goes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; premieres today. NPR's Eric Deggans notes that it exemplifies the tension between access and objectivity that filmmakers encounter when creating documentaries about celebrities.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;This week, it's an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/14/nx-s1-5448700/new-books-jeneva-rose-silvia-moreno-garcia" target="_blank"&gt;all-you-can-read buffet of new offerings&lt;/a&gt;, with flavors to suit virtually every palate. From a new horror novel from Silvia Moreno-Garcia to a short story collection about the American South by Carrie R. Moore.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/18/nx-s1-5438131/gabriela-ortiz-album-review-yanga" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yanga&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; features the vibrant colors, lively rhythms, melodic tunes, and bold concepts of Mexican composer Gabriela Ortiz. NPR's Tom Huizenga says the album is so good that it might get her a few more awards.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎮 Games: &lt;/strong&gt;NPR staff and contributors have examined the diverse offerings of the video game world so far this year. Whether you seek a brief distraction or an epic 50-hour adventure, here's an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/16/nx-s1-5459757/best-games-2025-picked-by-npr-staff" target="_blank"&gt;interactive list to help you find your next favorite game&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; Even the questions I didn't know, I answered correctly and ended up with a score of 10/11. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/18/g-s1-78018/trump-tennis-love-island-emmys-new-york-mayor" target="_blank"&gt;It's your turn&lt;/a&gt;. Do you think you can beat me?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-78076" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec8