l=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+171/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8c%2Ffc%2Fe1ec821b4051a72178e34a2d9681%2Fgettyimages-1240533062-1.jpg" class="img" alt="An illustration picture taken in London shows a gold-plated souvenir stablecoin issued by Tether." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 An illustration picture taken in London shows a gold-plated souvenir stablecoin issued by Tether.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Justin Tallis/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Congress passed the GENIUS bill yesterday, marking the country's first major standalone cryptocurrency bill. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/17/nx-s1-5451413/crypto-week-stablecoin-genius-act-trump" target="_blank"&gt;Here's what it does&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CBS has canceled &lt;em&gt;The Late Show with Stephen Colbert&lt;/em&gt;, the host announced during Thursday night's taping. The final show &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/17/nx-s1-5471581/cbs-stephen-colbert-late-show" target="_blank"&gt;will air in May&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pop singer Connie Francis — the first female singer to reach number one on the &lt;em&gt;Billboard &lt;/em&gt;Hot 100 — has died at 87. She &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/17/1238530020/connie-francis-dead" target="_blank"&gt;gained social media fame recently&lt;/a&gt; with the resurgence of her song "Pretty Little Baby."&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Obed Manuel&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
