gettyimages-579387320.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+170/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F1d%2F2de8b04d4cd68724d4383f2f0808%2Fgettyimages-579387320.jpg" class="img" alt="An Emmy statue in front of the Television Academy in 2016." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 An Emmy statue in front of the Television Academy in 2016.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Angela Weiss/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The nominations for the 2025 Primetime Emmy Awards were announced yesterday. Here is the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/15/nx-s1-5459779/2025-emmy-nominations-list" target="_blank"&gt;full list of nominees&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/15/nx-s1-5459780/2025-emmy-nominations-5-takeaways" target="_blank"&gt;takeaways&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A SpaceX capsule with four astronauts on the private Ax-4 mission splashed down in the Pacific Ocean off San Diego early yesterday, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/15/nx-s1-5467739/axiom-space-ax-4-spacex-iss-nasa-splashdown" target="_blank"&gt;concluding a 20-day journey in space&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Colorado's poet laureate, Andrea Gibson, &lt;a href="https://www.cpr.org/2025/07/14/colorado-poet-laureate-andrea-gibson-dies/" target="_blank"&gt;died at home&lt;/a&gt; on Monday from ovarian cancer. They were 49 years old. (via &lt;a href="https://www.cpr.org/" target="_blank"&gt;CPR&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
